02/10/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- One person died and four were injured in two explosions in Izmir on Tuesday (October 2nd). Two people were hurt in the first incident, outside a shopping centre in the district of Buca. The device was placed in a rubbish bin. The second bomb went off a few hours later at the same site, killing one person and injuring two others. No one has claimed responsibility for the attacks. (AFP, Reuters, AP, DPA, CNN Turk - 02/10/07) 
